Why Open Source? 
Open source is like making a Pizza (or having people help you make the pizza better)
Inspecting / Modifying / Finalizing source key
Tech conglomerates look to Git as your portfolio (make sure it's shiny) 
All software organizations are depended on open source software
Resume = show your employees you can code well
If they see an open source project that becomes recognise // Bonus points 

How does it work? 
All open source projects happen GitHub (like a DropBox for code) 
Version Control (most important part) = writing an essay (different saved edit history) - save different versions in chronological order 

